# Production Deployment

## Server

- **Host:** Ubuntu (41.72.157.26)
- **Path:** `/opt/rdmdev`
- **Domain:** https://rdmdev.co.za
- **SSH user:** `paul` (non-root; sudo available)
- **Git remote:** `https://github.com/vassago85/rdmdev.git` (branch: `main`)

## Stack layout on server

Reverse-proxied via a shared **Nginx Proxy Manager** container on the external network `nginx-proxy-manager_default`.

Three services in `docker-compose.prod.yml`:

- `rdmdev-app` — nginx + php-fpm 8.3 + supervisor (single image, `docker/Dockerfile`)
- `rdmdev-db` — `mysql:8.0`
- `rdmdev-scheduler` — same image as app, runs `artisan schedule:run` in a loop

Internal bridge network `rdmdev_rdmdev-internal` connects them.

## Full rebuild/update (copy-paste)

```bash
cd /opt/rdmdev \
  && git pull origin main \
  && docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build --no-cache app \
  && docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml up -d --force-recreate app scheduler
```

`--no-cache` ensures Vite rebuilds CSS/JS inside the Dockerfile.
Always recreate `app` + `scheduler` together (they share the same baked image).

## First-time install

```bash
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/vassago85/rdmdev/main/docker/install.sh | bash
```

The script is idempotent and handles: clone/pull, `.env` from template with
random DB passwords, build, up, healthcheck wait, optional admin-user prompt.

## NPM proxy host config

- Domain: `rdmdev.co.za` (and `www.rdmdev.co.za`)
- Forward to: `rdmdev-app:80`, scheme `http`
- Block Common Exploits: on
- Websockets: on
- SSL: Let's Encrypt + Force SSL + HTTP/2

## What the entrypoint handles automatically

- Creates `storage/`, `bootstrap/cache/` subdirs
- Sets `www-data` ownership + 775 permissions
- Waits for `db:3306`
- Tests DB credentials with PDO (fails fast on mismatch, with actionable error)
- Runs `php artisan migrate --force`
- Seeds on first boot only (checks if `services` table has rows)
- Clears + warms caches (`config`, `route`, `view`)
- Creates `storage:link`
- Hands off to supervisord (runs php-fpm + nginx)

## What you still do manually

- DNS: point `A rdmdev.co.za` + `www.rdmdev.co.za` to `41.72.157.26`
- Configure the NPM proxy host (see above)
- Create the first Filament admin user:
  ```bash
  docker compose -f /opt/rdmdev/docker-compose.prod.yml exec app php artisan make:filament-user
  ```
